---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const personSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Person",
  "name": "Alexandros Emmanouilidis",
  "alternateName": "Alex Emmanouilidis",
  "url": "https://alexemm.com",
  "image": "https://alexemm.com/images/alex-hero.jpg",
  "description": "Computer Science student at the University of Cyprus, national fencing champion, and fantasy writer based in Cyprus.",
  "jobTitle": "Computer Science Student",
  "alumniOf": {
    "@type": "CollegeOrUniversity",
    "name": "University of Cyprus",
    "url": "https://www.ucy.ac.cy"
  },
  "nationality": "Cypriot",
  "sameAs": [
    "https://instagram.com/alexandros_emmanouilides",
    "https://www.facebook.com/share/17GjSfEDzu/?mibextid=wwXIfr"
  ]
};
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Born in Sweden, raised in Cyprus. Orthodox Christian, elite fencer since age 6, CS student at UCY, and a fantasy writer in progress. Alex Emmanouilidis."
  schema={personSchema}
>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container--narrow">

      <span class="section-label">About</span>
      <h1>My story</h1>

      <div class="about-hero-img">
        <img
          src="/images/alex-hero.jpg"
          alt="Alexandros Emmanouilidis"
          width="720"
          height="420"
          loading="eager"
        />
      </div>

      <div class="about-body">
        <p>
          I was born in Sweden to a Greek-Cypriot father and a Russian mother. Growing up
          with Orthodox Christianity, Mediterranean warmth, and Slavic directness shaped how I
          see the world long before I had words for it. I've lived in Cyprus long enough to call
          it home, but the mix never fully settles. I speak Greek and English fluently, Russian
          well enough to get by, and I've learned that growing up between cultures either
          confuses you or makes you adaptable. It did the latter.
        </p>

        <h2 class="about-subhead">Fencing</h2>
        <p>
          The biggest thing that shaped me isn't on any CV. It's fencing. My father brought
          the sport to Cyprus and founded its first club. I picked up a sword at six years old
          and never really put it down. I became champion in every age category I competed in.
          I travelled to many countries competing at European and World events. I made the
          national team, competing with support from the federation and the Bank of Cyprus.
          At my last year as a Cadet, I became the first Cypriot to reach the Top 32 at both
          the European and World Championships.
        </p>
        <p>
          Fencing gave me discipline, drive, and a very specific relationship with losing. You
          compete alone on a piste, no team to blame, no referee to hide behind. Just you and
          what you've put into it. I lost plenty over the years. Each defeat taught me
          something the victories didn't.
        </p>
        <p>
          In July 2025, I fractured my right metacarpal. My sword hand. Two surgical nails in
          it for three months. I haven't fenced since. For someone who's been training since
          before they could read properly, that's a strange kind of quiet. I'm not done with
          fencing. But for now, I wait.
        </p>

        <div class="about-fencing-img">
          <img
            src="/images/alex-fencing-1.jpg"
            alt="Alexandros competing in fencing"
            width="720"
            height="480"
            loading="lazy"
          />
        </div>

        <h2 class="about-subhead">Family and service</h2>
        <p>
          I'm the oldest of five — three sisters and a brother, the youngest sixteen years my
          junior. Responsibility found me early. At eighteen, I served fourteen months in the
          Cypriot military. Mandatory, but not meaningless.
        </p>

        <h2 class="about-subhead">Computers and networks</h2>
        <p>
          Through all of it, I was falling in love with computers and networks. What started as
          curiosity in high school grew into something I couldn't ignore. Now I'm studying
          Computer Science at the University of Cyprus and interning at PwC this summer.
          Networking is where I want to specialise — the architecture of how things connect,
          how information moves, how systems hold together or fall apart.
        </p>

        <h2 class="about-subhead">Writing and worlds</h2>
        <p>
          Outside of CS, I fell in love with reading somewhere along the way. Fantasy above all
          else. Which is how I ended up building something of my own: a fantasy world from
          scratch. Not adapting anything, not borrowing a setting — building the mythology, the
          geography, the logic of that world, and eventually writing a full novel set inside it.
          Possibly many. That project moves slowly and deliberately, which suits it.
        </p>

        <h2 class="about-subhead">Faith</h2>
        <p>
          One more thing people tend to be surprised by: I'm a Greek Orthodox Christian, and I
          mean that sincerely. My faith isn't inherited habit. It's the result of years of
          research, reading, debate, and a lot of genuine searching. The more I look, the more
          convinced I become. That's not something I'll be argued out of. I also practise
          Byzantine music — the ancient choral tradition of the Church. Different from fencing,
          different from code, but the same instinct: find something worth going deep into, and
          go deep.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="about-links">
        <a href="/cv" class="btn btn--primary">See my CV</a>
        <a href="/portfolio" class="btn btn--ghost">Portfolio</a>
        <a href="/contact" class="btn btn--ghost">Get in touch</a>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  h1 {
    margin-top: var(--space-xs);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .about-hero-img {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
    border-radius: 6px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .about-hero-img img {
    width: 100%;
    height: 380px;
    object-fit: cover;
    object-position: center top;
  }

  .about-body {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .about-body p {
    max-width: 65ch;
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .about-subhead {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: var(--space-xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .about-fencing-img {
    margin-block: var(--space-xl);
    border-radius: 6px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .about-fencing-img img {
    width: 100%;
    height: 360px;
    object-fit: cover;
  }

  .about-links {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    padding-top: var(--space-lg);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .about-links {
      flex-direction: column;
    }
  }
</style>
